priority=\"high\" width=\"800\" height=\"539\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/jen-white-johnson-black-disabled-lives-matter-mural.png?resize=800%2C539&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"A prototype for a mural with the headline &quot;Say Their Names&quot; featuring a Black power fist with the infinity symbol and the words \u201cBlack Disabled Lives Matter\u201d written down the wrist of the fist. There are images that spell out &quot;BDLM&quot; in ASL and a list of names of Black Disabled people killed by police.\" class=\"wp-image-12071\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/jen-white-johnson-black-disabled-lives-matter-mural.png?resize=1024%2C690&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/jen-white-johnson-black-disabled-lives-matter-mural.png?resize=300%2C202&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/jen-white-johnson-black-disabled-lives-matter-mural.png?resize=768%2C517&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/jen-white-johnson-black-disabled-lives-matter-mural.png?resize=1536%2C1035&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/jen-white-johnson-black-disabled-lives-matter-mural.png?resize=2048%2C1380&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/jen-white-johnson-black-disabled-lives-matter-mural.png?w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><figcaption>image: Jen White Johnson<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p>Artist, designer, educator, and activist Jen White Johnson created several designs for mural projects honoring Black disabled individuals who were killed by police, as <a href=\"https:\/\/jenwhitejohnson.com\/About-Me-and-Contact\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">she writes<\/a>: <\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Since sharing the details of this mural, many disability collectives have reached out to me asking how they can create this mural in their hometowns! This online space is meant to be an online resource for my fellow BIPOC disabled folks to see how they can help and also have access to my vision and requirements on how the artwork can be produced and recreated!<\/p><p>The names you see in the mural concept are names of Black Disabled lives lost to state violence and systemic racism. The purpose of the mural is to highlight joy in the midst of resistance, amplifying that an all inclusive murals can continue to exist, furthering the message of decolonizing dreams.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn more about the <a href=\"https:\/\/jenwhitejohnson.com\/Black-Disabled-Lives-Matter-Mural-Project\">Black Disabled Lives Matter mural project<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Artist, designer, educator, and activist Jen White Johnson created several designs for mural projects honoring Black disabled individuals who were killed by police, as she writes: Since sharing the details of this mural, many disability collectives have reached out to me asking how they can create this mural in their&hellip; <a class=\"continue\" href=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/jen-white-johnson-black-disabled-lives-matter-mural-project\/\">Continue Reading<span> Jen White Johnson: Black Disabled Lives Matter Mural Project<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":12071,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"advanced_seo_description":"","jetpack_seo_html_title":"","jetpack_seo_noindex":false,"_FSMCFIC_featured_image_caption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_nocaption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_hide":""},"categories":[44],"ta